    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-10-14T01:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-10-14T01:00:00-05:00" n="375"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d375">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/12835: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Canton</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Paxton</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Canton</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-10-14T14:00:00+08:00"
                            >October 14, 1934—2 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received October 14—10:20 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>With reference to the Legation’s October 10, 5 [<hi rend="italic">4?</hi>]
                        p.m.<note n="68" xml:id="d375fn68">See telegram No. 460, October 10, 5 p.m.,
                        from the Chargé in China, <hi rend="italic">supra</hi>.</note> and
                    Ballantine’s October 10, midnight<note n="69" xml:id="d375fn69">Not found in
                        Department files. Joseph W. Ballantine, Consul General at Canton, had been
                        assigned to Mukden and relinquished his duties at Canton October 11,
                        1934.</note> regarding evacuation from Kweichow, I have received a telegram
                    in reply to his stating that Americans are withdrawing from eastern and northern
                    stations, women and children leaving Kweiyang. Concentration at Anshun and
                    Tuhshan. Repeated to the Department, the Legation, Nanking and Hankow. Yunnanfu
                    briefly informed.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Paxton</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
